{{Infobox language |name=Bomboli |nativename= |states=[[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] |ethnicity= |speakers=2,500 |date=1986 |ref = e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo languages|Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Bantoid languages|Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] ([[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone C|Zone C.10]]) |fam6=[[Ngondi–Ngiri languages|Ngondi–Ngiri]] |iso3=bml |glotto=bomb1261 |glottorefname=Bomboli |guthrie=C161 }}
'''Bomboli''' (also ''Bombongo'') is a [[Bantu language]] of the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]]. The language is spoken in the towns of [[Kungu]] and [[Dongo, Democratic Republic of the Congo|Dongo]] in the [[Sud-Ubangi]] province, specifically on a canal flowing into [[Ngiri River|Ngiri]] river, north of [[Bomongo]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.ethnologue.com/language/bml|title=Bomboli|work=Ethnologue|access-date=2017-04-22}}</ref>
The language has 3 dialects and is reportedly most similar to the [[Bozaba language|Bozaba]] and [[Bala language|Lobala]] languages.<ref name=":0" />
