{{use dmy dates|date=November 2012}} {{Infobox person |name = Camillo Cibin |image = Camillo Cibin 20051219.jpg |image_size = Camillo Cibin in 2005 |caption = |birth_name = |birth_date = {{birth date|1926|6|3|df=yes}} |birth_place = Salgareda |death_date = {{death date and age|2009|10|25|1926|6|3|df=yes}} |death_place = Rome |residence = |nationality = Italian |alma_mater = |occupation = Inspector General of the Vatican Gendarme Corps |years_active = |net_worth = |boards = |religion = |spouse = Maria Cibin |children = Three |parents = |signature = |website = }}
'''Camillo Cibin''' (3 June 1926 – 25 October 2009) was a [[Papal]] [[bodyguard]] and [[Inspector_General#Vatican_City|Inspector General]] of the [[Corps of Gendarmerie of Vatican City|Corpo della Gendarmeria]], the security and police force of [[Vatican City]]. He retired in 2006 after 58 years of service in the security force, and over 40 years as its commander.<ref name="six popes later">{{cite news|url=http://www.catholicnews.com/data/stories/cns/0603324.htm|archive-url=http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20091005061003/http://www.catholicnews.com/data/stories/cns/0603324.htm|dead-url=yes|archive-date=5 October 2009|title=Six popes later, Vatican security chief turns in his jogging shoes|author=Cindy Wooden|publisher=[[Catholic News Service]]|date=9 June 2006|accessdate=24 August 2007}}</ref> He served as a bodyguard to six popes.<ref name=independent9119>{{cite news|title=Camillo Cibin: Bodyguard to six popes who twice intervened in attempts on the life of John Paul II|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/obituaries/camillo-cibin-bodyguard-to-six-popes-who-twice-intervened-in-attempts-on-the-life-of-john-paul-ii-1817289.html|accessdate=3 November 2012|newspaper=The Independent|date=9 November 2009}}</ref>
==Early life and career== Cibin was born at [[Salgareda]], in the northern province of [[Province of Treviso|Treviso]] in Italy, on 3 June 1926.<ref name=ttel/> He joined the Vatican police force at age 21. He began serving in charge of security at the Vatican Council in the 1960s. He was appointed inspector-general of [[Vatican Gendarmerie|the Vatican Gendarmerie]] in 1972.<ref name=ttel/>
==Pope John Paul II Assassination attempt== Cibin was with [[Pope John Paul II]] when [[Pope John Paul II assassination attempt|he was shot]] in [[St. Peter's Square]] in 1981. Cibin captured [[Mehmet Ali Ağca]], who was convicted of the assassination attempt and spent 19 years in an Italian prison.<ref name="six popes later" /> A year later, Cibin prevented [[Juan María Fernández y Krohn]] from stabbing the pontiff during his visit to [[Fátima, Portugal|Fatima]].<ref name="WSJ obit">{{cite news| url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB125746370679932197|title=Security Chief for the Vatican Was 'Guardian Angel' to Pope|publisher=''[[Wall Street Journal]]''|date=6 November 2009|accessdate=6 June 2009}}</ref>
==Death and funeral== Cibin died at 83 of natural causes.<ref name="WSJ obit"/><ref name=ttel>{{cite news|title=Camillo Cibin|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/religion-obituaries/6509534/Camillo-Cibin.html|accessdate=3 November 2012|newspaper=The Telegraph|date=5 November 2009}}</ref> His funeral mass was performed in [[St. Peter's Square]] in the Vatican City.<ref name=independent9119/>
