{{Infobox company | name = Correios de Cabo Verde | logo = | image =File:Praia-Correos.jpg | image_size = | image_caption=Headquarters of Correios de Cabo Verde (Post of Cape Verde or Cape Verde Post)]] | type = [[Limited liability company|SARL]] | foundation = 1 January 1995 | location = Rua Cesário de Lacerda 2, 7600 [[Praia]], [[Cape Verde]] | owner = | head = | key_people = | num_employees = | industry = | homepage = {{url |http://www.correios.cv/}} }} '''Correios de Cabo Verde''' (Portuguese for Post of Cape Verde) is the company responsible for [[mail|postal service]] in [[Cape Verde]]. The headquarters of the company are in the [[Plateau (Praia)|city centre]] of [[Praia]], at Rua Cesário Lacerda, nº 2.<ref>[http://www.correios.cv/conteudo.aspx?id=1604 Contactos], Correios de Cabo Verde</ref>
==History== During Portuguese rule in Cape Verde which lasted until 1975, all postal services were done by [[Correios de Portugal]] (Portuguese Post). Its first post office was opened in Praia in 1849.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.correios.cv/conteudo.aspx?id=1588&cid=1606 |title=Correios De Cabo Verde |publisher=Correios.cv |date= |accessdate=2017-11-24}}</ref> Under law no. 9-A/95 made on 16 February 1995, the public company of posts and telecommunications (Empresa Pública dos Correios e Telecomunicaçöes, (CTT-EP) was split into two: Correios de Cabo Verde (postal service) and [[Cabo Verde Telecom]] (telecommunications). Both became [[Limited liability company|anonymous societies with limited responsibility]].<ref>[http://www.correios.cv/conteudo.aspx?id=1588&cid=1606 Quem somos], Correios de Cabo Verde</ref>
==Street names and numbers== More than 90% of Cape Verdean roads don't have names.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rinckes |first1=Doug |title=Delivering mail where streets have no name |url=https://africa.googleblog.com/2016/12/delivering-mail-where-streets-have-no.html |website=Official Google Africa Blog |publisher=Google}}</ref> As such, most people use community post boxes. To enable delivery at home, the [[Open Location Code]] system invented by [[Google]] has officially been adopted by the Cape Verdean post, including a system on their website to officially link their home location with personal data at the post office.<ref>{{cite web |title=Morada Certa |url=http://www.correios.cv/conteudo.aspx?id=1786&cid=1803 |website=www.correios.cv |publisher=Correios Cabo Verde |language=Portuguese}}</ref>
