The '''Danish Social Service Law''', '''Serviceloven''', properly ''Lov om social service'',  is a [[Denmark|Danish]] [[law]] which specifies guidelines for advice and support both in order to prevent [[social problem]]s and to provide services to people with physical or mental disabilities or particular social problems.

The first version of the law was passed in 1998, but it is typically revised several times a year, {{As of|2014|06|19|lc=yes}} most recently on 10 June 2014.<ref>[https://www.retsinformation.dk/Forms/r0710.aspx?id=163646 "Lov om ændring af lov om social service og lov om forpligtende kommunale samarbejder"], LOV nr 576 § 1, 10 June 2014; [https://www.retsinformation.dk/Forms/r0710.aspx?id=163647 "Lov om ændring af lov om social service"], LOV nr 577, 10 June 2014, at retsinformation.dk {{da icon}}</ref>

