{{ infobox windmill | name = Hørsholm Windmill | image = [[File:Hørsholm Mølle 2.jpg|200px]] | caption = | name_of_mill = Hørsholm Windmill | location_of_mill = [[Hørsholm]], Denmark | coordinates = {{coord|55.99600|11.96646|format=dms|type:landmark_region:DK|display=inline,title}} | operator = | built = 1892 | purpose = [[grist mill|Corn mill]] | type = [[Smock mill]] | storeys = Three storey smock | base_storeys = Single storey base | smock_sides = Eight sides | sail_number = Four sails | sail_type = [[windmill sail#Common sails|Common Sails]] | windshaft = | winding = | fantail_blades = | auxpower = | pairs_of_millstones= | stone_size = | lost = | other = }}
'''Hørsholm Windmill''' ([[Danish language|Danish]]. Hørsholm Mølle) is a [[smock mill]] located in [[Hørsholm]] to the north of [[Copenhagen]], Denmark. The site also comprises two storage buildings. The complex is now home to a small museum of old crafts.
==History== The windmill was constructed in 1890&ndash;91 by mill builder Martin Johansen. ItWind power was already falling out of facour and it was supplemented by a steam engine in 1895 and by a diesel engine from 1914. One large and two small electrical engines were installed in about 1940 and the complex was from then on used for production of chicken ffeed. It was decommissioned in the 1970s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://horsholmhf.dk/side7.html|title=Hørsholm Mølle|language=Danish|website=Håndværkerforeningen|accessdate=28 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.moellearkivet.dk/egeskov-mlle|title=HØRSHOLM MØLLE, Ved Møllen 8, 2970 Hørsholm|language=Danish|website=Moellearkivet.dk|accessdate=28 May 2016}}</ref>
==Description== The windmill consists of an octagonal tower clad in [[wood shingle|shingles]] and topped by an ogee cap. The cap carries the four [[windmill sail#Common sails|Common sails]]. It is winded by a fantail. The mill stands on a dressed brick case, which has an underpass for wagons.
==Today== The windmill is now home to a small museum of traditional crafts. It was opened by the Association of Craftsmen in Copenhagen. The premises are also rented out for exhibitions and other events.
==See also== * [[List of windmills in Denmark]]
