{{Infobox station | name = [[File:Sofia Metro Logo.svg|30px|left|link=Sofia Metro]] James Bourchier | type = | style = Sofia Metro | image = Джеймс Баучер.jpg | image_caption = | address = | coordinates = {{Coord|42|40|12.50|N|23|19|12.50|E|type:railwaystation_region:BG-23|display=inline,title}} | line = <!-- line information is detailed under "services" --> | other = | structure = sub-surface | platform = side | depth = 28 m | levels = 4 and 5 | tracks = 2 | parking = 650 parking lots | bicycle = | baggage_check = | opened = 31-Aug-2012 | closed = | rebuilt = | electrified = | ADA = | code = 2977; 2978 | owned = [[Sofia#Administration|Sofia Municipality]] | zone = | smartcardname = | smartcardstatus = | former = Lozenets / Cherni vrah Blvd. | passengers = | pass_year = | pass_percent = | pass_system = | mpassengers = | services = {{s-rail|title=Sofia Metro}} {{s-line|system=Sofia Metro|line=Line 2|previous=Vitosha|next=European Union}} | map_locator = [[File:Map8 eng trans.png|300px]] | web = }} {{Sofia Metro Blue line}} '''James Bourchier Metro Station''' ({{lang-bg|Метростанция "Джеймс Баучер"}}) is a station on the [[Sofia Metro]] in [[Bulgaria]], named after [[James David Bourchier]]. It was put into operation on August 31, 2012. Bulgaria's PM [[Boyko Borisov]] and the [[President of the European Commission]] [[Jose Manuel Barroso]] inaugurated the new section of the Sofia Metro, which was funded with EU money.<ref>http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=142808</ref><ref>http://www.focus-fen.net/index.php?id=n286275</ref> The initial project name of the Metro Station was Lozenets named after the neighbourhood [[Lozenets, Sofia|Lozenets]].
A [[Park and ride|park-and-ride]] underground facility with 650 parking lots was built along with the construction of the James Bourchier Station.<ref>{{cite news|title=Завършен е и третият буферен паркинг по линията на метрото|url=http://infrastructure.bg/show.php?storyid=1947068|publisher=infrastructure.bg|date=15 November 2012|language=Bulgarian}}</ref>
