{{Infobox broadcasting network | name = Kantipur FM | image = | logo = | type = [[FM station]] | branding = | established = | test card = | test of transmission = | airdate = | country = {{flagcountry|Nepal}} | founded = {{Start date|1998|10}}
| slogan = Station of the Nation (रेडियो राष्ट्रको) | motto = | market_share = | license_area = | headquarters = [[Kathmandu]] | broadcast_area = | area = | erp = | owner = | parent = [[Kantipur Publications]] | key_people = {{Unbulleted list | Kailash Sirohiya (Director) | Subekshya K.C }} | foundation = | launch_date = | dissolved = | former_names = Radio Rastra ko | digital = | analog = {{Unbulleted list | 96.1&nbsp;MHz (East/Central) | 101.8&nbsp;MHz (West) }} | callsigns = | callsign_meaning = | former_callsigns = | affiliation = | affiliates = | groups = | former_affiliations = | webcast = {{Unbulleted list | {{URL|radiokantipur.com/live}} | {{URL|www.livefms.net/2011/06/kantipur-fm.html}} }} | website = {{URL|radiokantipur.com}} | footnotes = }} '''Kantipur FM''' ({{Lang-ne|कान्तिपुर एफ. एम.}}) or '''Radio Kantipur''' ({{Lang-ne|रेडियो कान्तिपुर}}) is a [[Nepal]]ese [[FM radio|FM radio station]], established in October 1998.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1900787341.html|title=Radio Kantipur marks 11th anniversary|last=|first=|date=13 November 2009|work=The Kathmandu Post|access-date=14 February 2018|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|subscription=yes|via=HighBeam Research}}</ref> It currently operates in the eastern, central, western, mid-western and far-western development regions. It is most popular in eastern region and in [[Kathmandu]]. It provides news and entertainment programs 24 hours a day. In 2007 it started nationwide transmission on two frequencies&nbsp;– 96.1&nbsp;MHz in the east and central regions and 101.8&nbsp;MHz in the west. Additionally, it is available via the internet at [http://radiokantipur.ekantipur.com/live www.radiokantipur.com/live ].
==Relay Stations== * 96.1 in [[Kathmandu]] * 96.1 in [[Bhedetar]] [[Dhankuta district|Dhankuta]] * 96.1 in [[Birgunj|Birgunj, Parsa]] * 96.1 in [[Bharatpur, Nepal|Bharatpur, Chitwan]] * 96.1 in [[Bhairahawa|Bhairahawa, Rupandehi]] * 101.8 in [[Nepalgunj|Nepalgunj, Banke]] * 101.8 in [[Pokhara|Pokhara, Kaski]] * 101.8 in [[Dhangadhi|Dhangadi, Kailali]]
