{{Infobox musical artist | name = Nikos Ganos | image = https://s-media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/236x/91/09/b6/9109b63191f1e9e53ebf9bd98209df6a.jpg | image_size = | landscape = | alt = | caption = | background = solo_singer | birth_name = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | alias = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1983|7|22}} | birth_place = [[Athens]], [[Attica]], [[Greece]]
| death_date = | death_place = | genre = [[Pop music|Pop]], [[R&B]], [[Dance music|dance]] | occupation = [[Singer]], [[Model (people)|Model]] | instrument = | years_active = 2003-present | label = Heaven Music, Spin Records | associated_acts = | website = }}
'''Nikos Ganos''' ([[Greek language|Greek]]: ''Νίκος Γκάνος''; born 22 July 1983), also known as '''Nicko''', is a Greek [[singer]] and [[model (people)|model]].
==Career== In 2004, '''Nikos Ganos''' participated in the first and only series of [[Super Idol (Greek TV series)|Super Idol]], the former Greek version of the British talent show hit [[Pop Idol]]. He was in the "Bottom 2 or 3" from weeks four to seven and was eliminated in third place on week eight, the last week before the final. Since then '''Ganos''' has continued to release singles that have become hits in [[Greece]] and has worked with some of the biggest names of the Greek music scene like [[Giannis Parios]], [[Kaiti Garbi]], [[Giorgos Mazonakis]] and [[Marinella]]. In 2010 he released the song ''"Last Summer"'' which was the most successful song in Greece that year. In 2011 he performed ''"Last Summer"'' live on [[The X Factor (Greece series 3)|X Factor Greece]]. In 2012, he performed ''"Break Me In The Dark"'' (a remix of ''"Break Me"'') with [[Katerina Stikoudi]] at the [[MAD Video Music Awards]]. In 2013 he released his new song ''"I'm in love"''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.similar-artists.com/similarto/artist/Nikos%20Ganos//|title=About Nikos Ganos|work=similar-artists.com}}</ref> In April 2013, '''Ganos''' has been competing in the first Greek series of [[Your Face Sounds Familiar (season 1)|Your Face Sounds Familiar]] and was eliminated in week 12. Each week he transformed and performed song by famous singers like; [[George Michael]], [[Justin Timberlake]], [[John Lennon]], [[Notis Sfakianakis]], [[Justin Bieber]], Giorgos Mazonakis, [[Prince (musician)|Prince]], Zozo Sapountzaki, and winner of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2003]], [[Sertab Erener]]. '''Ganos''' himself has shown interest in representing [[Greece in the Eurovision Song Contest|Greece at the Eurovision Song Contest]] in the past.
==Personal life== Nikos Ganos was born and lives in [[Athens]], [[Greece]]. He has toured around Greece. He has two tattoos, one of an [[Ancient Greece|ancient Greek]] Soldier's helmet on his back and "Family Tree" written in [[Hindi]] on his left arm.
