{{Infobox Airport | name = Orapa Airport | nativename = | image = | IATA = ORP | ICAO = FBOR | pushpin_map = Botswana | pushpin_map_caption = Location of airport in Botswana | pushpin_label = '''ORP''' | pushpin_label_position = bottom | FAA = | type = Public | owner = [[Debswana]] | operator = | location = [[Orapa]], [[Botswana]] | elevation-f = 3100 | elevation-m = | coordinates = {{coord|21|16|00|S|25|19|05|E|region:BW_type:airport|display=inline,title}} | website = | metric-rwy = y | r1-number = 07/25 | r1-length-m = 1675 | r1-length-f = | r1-surface = Asphalt | footnotes = Source: SkyVector<ref name="DCA">[https://skyvector.com/airport/FBOR/Orapa-Airport SkyVector - Orapa]</ref> GCM<ref>{{GCM|ORP|Orapa Airport}}</ref> }}
'''Orapa Airport''' {{airport codes|ORP|FBOR}} is an airport serving [[Orapa]], a town in the [[Central District (Botswana)|Central District]] of [[Botswana]]. It is owned by [[Debswana]], which also owns the [[Orapa diamond mine]].
There is no scheduled airline service. Landing permission must be obtained from Debswana at least 48 hours prior to arrival. Orapa is an airport of entry and departure for common customs only. Immigration should handled through Botswana's international airports.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.caab.co.bw/caab-content.php?cid=261|title=caab botswana civil aviation botswana aeronautical navigation aircraft licensing botswana 09-12-13|last=cityweb.in|website=www.caab.co.bw|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref>
The Orapa [[non-directional beacon]] (Ident: '''OR''') is located on the field.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ourairports.com/navaids/OR/Orapa_NDB_BW/#lat=-21.268600463867188,lon=25.301300048828125,zoom=10,type=Satellite|title=Orapa NDB (OR) @ OurAirports|website=ourairports.com|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref>
